## Documentation Sources

DebOps documentation lives in several places. Use the right source for the
information you need.

### 1. Role default variables

The authoritative source for default variable names, types, and values is the
role's ``defaults/`` directory inside the DebOps monorepo. These files are
**not** duplicated in ``docs/`` - they are included into the Sphinx-built
documentation at runtime.

Load the ``debops-find-source`` skill to locate the monorepo, then read:

```
ansible/roles/<role>/defaults/main.yml
```

Some roles define defaults across multiple files in that directory.

### 2. Role documentation (with examples)

ReadTheDocs at ``https://docs.debops.org/`` includes the full role documentation
with default variables expanded. Useful when the monorepo is not available.

Available documentation versions on ReadTheDocs:

| URL slug | Content |
|---|---|
| ``latest`` | Latest development build (git default branch) |
| ``master`` | Alias for ``latest`` |
| ``v<X.Y.Z>`` | Specific release (e.g. ``v3.2.0``) |
| ``stable-<X>.<Y>`` | Stable release branch (e.g. ``stable-3.2``) |

Determine the installed DebOps version to pick the closest match:

```sh
debops --version
# or
python3 -c "import debops; print(debops.__version__)"
```

Then construct the URL (append ``index.html`` for the role overview):

```
https://docs.debops.org/en/latest/ansible/roles/<role>/index.html
https://docs.debops.org/en/v<X.Y.Z>/ansible/roles/<role>/index.html
https://docs.debops.org/en/stable-<X>.<Y>/ansible/roles/<role>/index.html
```

For detailed variable examples, use ``defaults-detailed.html``:

```
https://docs.debops.org/en/latest/ansible/roles/<role>/defaults-detailed.html
```

### 3. Role manpage

When DebOps is installed as a Python package, manpages are available:

```sh
man debops.<role> 5
```

Role manpages describe the role's purpose and structure but do **not** include
default variable documentation. Fall back to the monorepo or ReadTheDocs for
variable details.

### 4. Subcommand documentation

For ``debops run``, ``debops check``, and other subcommands:

```sh
man debops-run 5
man debops-check 5
man debops-exec 5
man debops-project 5
```

Without manpages, use ReadTheDocs:

```
https://docs.debops.org/en/latest/user-guide/scripts/debops-run/debops-run.html
https://docs.debops.org/en/latest/user-guide/scripts/debops-check/debops-check.html
```

### 5. Agent conventions

The project's agent usage conventions are documented in
``docs/user-guide/ai-agent-integration.rst`` in the monorepo (or on
ReadTheDocs).

### 6. General / changelog

- Monorepo ``docs/`` directory - raw RST source for Sphinx
- ReadTheDocs ``https://docs.debops.org/en/latest/index.html`` - rendered HTML
- ``docs/news/`` - changelog

## Source selection summary

| You need... | Use... |
|---|---|
| Variable names and values | ``ansible/roles/<role>/defaults/main.yml`` in the monorepo |
| Variable docs with examples | ReadTheDocs ``/en/latest/ansible/roles/<role>/index.html`` |
| Role synopsis / structure | ``man debops.<role> 5`` |
| Subcommand usage | ``man debops-<subcommand> 5`` or ReadTheDocs |
| General browsing | ReadTheDocs ``/en/latest/index.html`` |
